HEADWORD: Lettic
<hw>Let"tic</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧t"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Of or pertaining to the Letts; Lettish.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of
or pertaining to a branch of the Slavic family, subdivided into Lettish,
Lithuanian, and Old Prussian.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The language of the Letts; Lettish.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
language of the Lettic race, including Lettish, Lithuanian, and Old
Prussian.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
